		<title>04Coal in Ferryhill</title>
		<content> Coal has been very important to the   
 development of Ferryhill.The first    
 mention of mining here is 1347 when   
 Robert Todd and Hugh Smyth paid the   
 Abbey of Durham for mining rights in  
 Ferryhill.The first pits were bell    
 pits with a maximum height of         
 30metres.                             
 These are the mines in our area with  
 their opening dates:-                 
 1867:Thrislington                     
 1872:Chilton Dene Bridge              
 1873:East Howle                       
 1874:Windlestone                      
 1902:Dean and Chapter                 
 1904:Mainsforth                       
 None are working today.               
            Michael Clarey(age 11)     
                                       
                                       
                                       
